joins - joins are used to combine data from two or more tables based on a related column

1. inner join - used to return only matching records from both tables
              - it return c_name, emp_name and salry 
                    select c.c_name,e.emp_name,e.salary 
                    from company c
                    inner join Employees e
                    on c.emp_id = e.Emp_id;

             - Another way 

                    select * from employees
                    join company
                    on company.emp_id=Employees.emp_id;
Natural join - Automatically joins same column
             - in inner join we must specify column but here no need
                   select * from company 
                    natural join Employees;
2. left join - used to return all records from the left table and matching records from the right table
                 
                    select c.c_name,e.emp_name,e.salary 
                    from company c
                    left join Employees e
                    on c.emp_id = e.Emp_id;

3. right join - used to return all records from the right table and matching records from the left table

                    select c.c_name,e.emp_name,e.salary 
                    from company c
                    right join Employees e
                    on c.emp_id = e.Emp_id;

4. full outer join -it return all the records from both tables and fill with null if there is no match

                    select c.c_name,e.emp_name,e.salary 
                    from company c
                    full join Employees e
                    on c.emp_id = e.Emp_id;

5. self join - used to join a table with itself
                 - it is used to compare rows within the same table (<> - not equal)

                    select e1.emp_name,e2.emp_name
                    from Employees e1
                    join Employees e2
                    on e1.dept_id = e2.dept_id
                    and e1.emp_id <> e2.emp_id;

6. cross join - used to return the Cartesian product of the two tables
                 - it return all possible combinations of rows from both tables

                    select c.c_name,e.emp_name,e.salary
                    from company c
                    cross join Employees e;

